ty within Bohemian Jewry – the German-Jewish, the Czech-Jewish and the Zionist. This book provides a needed framework for understanding the rich history of German- and Czech-Jewish politics and culture in Bohemia and is a notable contribution to the historiography of Bohemian, Czechoslovak and central European Jewry.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 27. Jan 2023) 0aJewsxHistoryx20th centuryxCzech RepublicxBohemia. 0aJewsxIdentityxCzech RepublicxBohemia. 0aJewsxSocial conditionsx20th centuryxCzech RepublicxBohemia. 0aJewszCzech RepubliczBohemiaxHistoryy20th century. 0aJewszCzech RepubliczBohemiaxIdentity. 0aJewszCzech RepubliczBohemiaxSocial conditionsy20th century. 7aHISTORY / Jewish.2bisacsh  aJewish Studies, History (General).08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertBerghahn Books Complete eBook-Package 2000-2013z978311099828340uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978085745475140uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780857454751423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780857454751/original  a978-3-11-099828-3  Berghahn Books Complete eBook-Package 2000-2013c2000d2013  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_HICS  aEBA_EBACKALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_HICS  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_PPALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA13ENGE  aPDA17SSHEE  aPDA5EBK